}
```

This seems iterative too. The issue might be in the recursive call pattern within the state machine. When processing the end tag, there could be a recursive call chain that creates the stack overflow.

Looking at the test more carefully, the generated HTML is like:
`0<dl><dd>1<dl><dd>2<dl><dd>...24999<dl><dd>0</dd></dl>1</dd></dl>...24999</dd></dl>`

So after parsing the first part, the stack will have 25,000 `<dd>` elements on it (inside `<dl>` elements), and when processing the closing tags, the parser might be making recursive calls.

